htened presence elsewhere in the Middle East and in Africa. As such, Rules of Disengagement provides inspiration and lessons for anyone who opposes an interventionist U.S. military policy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAfghan War, 2001-2021xMoral and ethical aspects. 0aIraq War, 2003-2011xMoral and ethical aspects. 0aMilitary ethicszUnited States. 0aSelective conscientious objectionzUnited States. 0aSoldiersxLegal status, laws, etc.zUnited States. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975xMoral and ethical aspects. 0aWarxMoral and ethical aspectszUnited States. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh1 aGilberd, Kathleen, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978098157692340uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814762929.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814762929423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814762929/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK